snippet.textDisplay: I'm a Giants fan and have watched just about every snap this year.  If you are an Eagles fan, you should be very concerned that your team struggled in this game.  These 2-11 Giants are dysfunctional on many levels, have one of the youngest rosters in the NFL, have terrible coaching, absolutely sickeningly bad defense, bottom 5 team on pass protection and pass rush, some of the worst receiver separation, riddled with injuries... I could go on.  They are literally 2-3 full seasons away from being a competitive, competent football team.  The fact that the Eagles, at home, ESCAPED with a victory in OT is pathetic.  The NFC east is absolute trash this year, and whatever sad sack team limps into the playoffs will be obliterated in the first round.  It's not even a question.
